metadata.title: Music For Installations
description: Musician, artist, thinker, activist Brian Eno first came to international prominence in the early '70s as a founding member of Roxy Music, and immediately followed by a series of highly acclaimed solo albums. His visionary production work includes albums with U2, David Bowie, Talking Heads, Coldplay and many others. Clam-shell box set w/6 die-cut wallets and 64 page Plexiglas bound book.
